<Content>Terrible The so-called beach was about 100 feet long., that was it...the mattress in Rm 118 were terrible...both beds were covered in vinyl and were so hard it would have been better to sleep on the floor. The bed spreads were dirty and stained. No wash cloths provided and none available when asked. Ice was kept in a cooler by the front desk...half melted. After a rain, the walk ways were flooded up to the outside doors of some of the rooms. You had to wear a paper wrist band the entire time you were there so they would know you were a quest at the hotel. We found this Hotel on the Internet and the pictures are very deceiving. The swimming pool was littered with leaves and very small. Would not recommend this hotel to anyone. Save your money and go to a Holiday Inn... 
