<Author>IJK01
<Content>Little beach hotel on seafood row We checked into this small beach front hotel for one night and extended our stay, day by day, for three additional nights., each at $90 per. Staff and manager couldn't have been more helpful, they even let us use their front desk PC to view Trip Advisor to help plan our next stop in Ponce. When we were there in mid-January the place was almost empty but the snack bar/restaurant was open daily so we could grab coffee or whatever each morning.The hotel has a small, very secluded, private beach which is shared with the low rise condo next store. Room was large and clean but sparsely furnished.A nice get away from it all place during the slow winter season in these parts. 
