<Author>akerl50544
<Content>Definately not the place!! we went to the joyuda beach resort 12/26/04 thru 12/29 04. we were not expecting anything great. we traveled p.r. for 10 days for the second time and once out of san juan your not really going to get fancy hotels. this hotel looked ok fom the outside. checked in at 11:00 a.m. the would not let us into the room until 4:00 even though there was hardly anyone there. no problem there were plenty of restaurants in the area to have lunch. we got into the hotel room. after a little examination the place is not really kept up. mold in the corners as well as all along the bottom of the tub, nevermind 6 or 7 guwee things on the bathroom door. still no problem, i was not expecting much. we got settled in and went to the hotel beach. there is about 20 ft of sand, total rocks as soon as you touch the water. no swimming! might not be a problem for some people but it is a non smoking hotel inside and out. we went out exploring, down to boquonron (cool little town) as well as the el faro (lighthouse) as well as a couple of cool beaches. came back to the hotel then went out for dinner in joyuda (ok). went to bed, to my surprise the king bed matress is wrapped in plastic and fitted with 2 sets of twin flat sheets which were wrapped around us in the morning with parts of our bodies on the plastic. still ok with it. went to get a shower, it pretty much dribbled out. i went to the desk to complain. she said she would take care of it. we took off for the afternoon, came back, still a dribble. complained again, said the maintenance person is no longer there, they will fix it in the morning. morning came and still no shower and then we left. i wasn't expecting to much but a shower that worked corectly is 1 of the most important, never mind the cleanliness and bed. simply we will never go back again even though we will be back to cabo rojo. 
